<div class="postdate">October 29, 2025</div>
<div class="posts">
<ul><li>
Kudos to Siemens EDA and the IEEE CEDA Design Automation Technical Committee for the collaborative efforts that resulted in the first-ever public reporting of benchmark results for a commercial place-and-route tool (Siemens EDA's Aprisa), with permission of the tool vendor. This breakthrough finally enables EDA researchers to see their field's leading edge in a clear, reproducible and sharable way. Our ICCAD-2025 paper (.pdf) is <a href="./Publications/Conferences/419/c419.pdf">HERE</a> (please see Section II), and the ICCAD-2025 presentation slides (.pptx) are <a href="./Publications/Conferences/419/c419.pptx">HERE</a>. Please also see the IEEE CEDA DATC GitHub repository, <a href="https://github.com/ieee-ceda-datc/First-Commercial-Benchmarking-SiemensEDA">HERE</a>.
</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="postdate">October 28, 2025</div>
<div class="posts">
<ul><li>
We are incredibly grateful that our project, "Trustworthy and Secure Cloud-Native Agentic OpenROAD", has been selected for an award as part of the <a href="https://nairrpilot.org/opportunities/deep-partnerships">Microsoft/NAIRR Pilot call for grand challenges and deep partnerships</a>. Huge thanks to Microsoft Azure and the NAIRR Pilot program for this fantastic boost to our research!
</li>
</ul>
</div>

